## Summary

Implement the full Bauhaus design system as a Flutter ThemeData with custom color scheme, typography, and reusable Bauhaus components (ghost blocks, heavy dividers, custom buttons, toggle switches).

## Implementation Details

### 1. Color scheme (`lib/core/theme/colors.dart`)

Define the full Material3 color scheme using the Bauhaus palette:

```dart
class BauhausColors {
  // Primary (Tomato Red)
  static const primary = Color(0xFFB12C16);
  static const primaryContainer = Color(0xFFFF6347);
  static const onPrimary = Color(0xFFFFFFFF);
  static const onPrimaryContainer = Color(0xFF630900);

  // Secondary (Bauhaus Blue)
  static const secondary = Color(0xFF0001C0);
  static const secondaryContainer = Color(0xFF080CFF);
  static const onSecondary = Color(0xFFFFFFFF);
  static const onSecondaryContainer = Color(0xFFB6BAFF);

  // Tertiary (Primary Yellow)
  static const tertiary = Color(0xFF705D00);
  static const tertiaryContainer = Color(0xFFC9A900);
  static const onTertiary = Color(0xFFFFFFFF);
  static const onTertiaryContainer = Color(0xFF4C3F00);

  // Neutrals
  static const surface = Color(0xFFF9F9F9);
  static const surfaceContainerLowest = Color(0xFFFFFFFF);
  static const surfaceContainerLow = Color(0xFFF3F3F3);
  static const surfaceContainer = Color(0xFFEEEEEE);
  static const surfaceContainerHigh = Color(0xFFE8E8E8);
  static const surfaceContainerHighest = Color(0xFFE2E2E2);
  static const onSurface = Color(0xFF1B1B1B);
  static const onSurfaceVariant = Color(0xFF5A413C);
  static const outline = Color(0xFF8E706B);
  static const outlineVariant = Color(0xFFE2BFB8);

  // Error
  static const error = Color(0xFFBA1A1A);
  static const errorContainer = Color(0xFFFFDAD6);
  static const onError = Color(0xFFFFFFFF);
}
```

### 2. Typography (`lib/core/theme/typography.dart`)

Use `google_fonts` package:

- **Display/Headline:** `GoogleFonts.spaceGrotesk()` — weight 900 (Black), uppercase, letter-spacing -0.02em
- **Body:** `GoogleFonts.inter()` — weight 400/700
- **Label:** `GoogleFonts.inter()` — weight 700, uppercase, letter-spacing 0.1em, fontSize 10-12

Build a full `TextTheme` and apply via `ThemeData.textTheme`.

### 3. Theme (`lib/core/theme/bauhaus_theme.dart`)

Create `ThemeData` with:
- The color scheme from step 1
- The text theme from step 2
- `borderRadius: 0` on all component themes (CardTheme, ButtonTheme, InputDecorationTheme, DialogTheme, etc.)
- `dividerTheme: DividerThemeData(thickness: 2, color: onSurface)`
- No elevation/shadows on any component — depth via ghost blocks only
- `appBarTheme` with 0 elevation, transparent background, `Border(bottom: BorderSide(width: 4, color: onSurface))`

### 4. Reusable Bauhaus widgets

#### `ghost_block.dart`
A wrapper widget that renders a solid `#1B1B1B` rectangle offset behind its child. Props: `offset` (default 4px), `child`. Uses `Stack` with a `Positioned` background and the child on top. Supports `onPressed` with translate animation (child moves into the ghost on press).

#### `bauhaus_app_bar.dart`
Fixed top bar: hamburger menu left, "BAUHAUS POMODORO" title (Space Grotesk, Black, uppercase, tight tracking), settings icon right. 4px bottom border in `onSurface`.

#### `bauhaus_nav_bar.dart`
Fixed bottom nav: 4 icons (timer, list_alt, bar_chart, person). Active icon gets a filled circle (`primaryContainer`) with 2px `onSurface` border. 4px top border. Takes `currentIndex` and `onTap`.

#### `bauhaus_button.dart`
Primary variant: sharp rectangle, `primary` background, white text, Space Grotesk bold uppercase, wrapped in `GhostBlock`. On press: translates 2px into ghost block.
Secondary variant: transparent background, 2px `onSurface` border, `onSurface` text.

#### `bauhaus_toggle.dart`
Custom toggle switch matching the design: 2px `onSurface` border rectangle, split into two halves (on/off). Active side fills with `onSurface`, indicator square is `primary` (on) or `surfaceContainerHighest` (off). No rounded corners.

#### `heavy_divider.dart`
Simple `Container` with configurable thickness (2/4/8px) and full-width `onSurface` background. Supports partial-width accent color overlay (e.g., 1/4 width in `primary`).

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `BauhausTheme.light()` returns a complete ThemeData
- [ ] All text uses Space Grotesk (headlines) or Inter (body/labels) via google_fonts
- [ ] Zero border-radius on all Material components
- [ ] GhostBlock widget renders offset shadow and animates on press
- [ ] BauhausAppBar renders with 4px bottom border and correct typography
- [ ] BauhausNavBar highlights active tab with filled circle
- [ ] BauhausButton primary and secondary variants match the design
- [ ] BauhausToggle switch animates between on/off states
- [ ] HeavyDivider renders at 2/4/8px thicknesses
- [ ] `flutter analyze` passes

