## Summary

Implement the task management data layer: create, read, update, delete tasks with priority levels, pomodoro estimates, and status tracking.

## Implementation Details

### 1. Task Repository (`lib/data/repositories/task_repository.dart`)

```dart
class TaskRepository {
  final AppDatabase db;

  Future<List<PomodoroTask>> getAllTasks()
  Future<List<PomodoroTask>> getTasksByStatus(TaskStatus status)
  Future<PomodoroTask?> getActiveTask()  // status == active
  Future<PomodoroTask?> getTaskById(String id)
  Future<void> createTask(PomodoroTask task)
  Future<void> updateTask(PomodoroTask task)
  Future<void> deleteTask(String id)
  Future<void> setTaskActive(String id)  // Sets status to active, deactivates any other active task
  Future<void> completeTask(String id)   // Sets status to completed + completedAt
  Future<void> incrementPomodoros(String id)  // completedPomodoros += 1
  Stream<List<PomodoroTask>> watchAllTasks()  // Reactive stream for UI
}
```

### 2. Riverpod providers

```dart
final taskRepositoryProvider = Provider((ref) =>
    TaskRepository(ref.watch(databaseProvider)));

// Reactive task list
final allTasksProvider = StreamProvider<List<PomodoroTask>>((ref) {
  return ref.watch(taskRepositoryProvider).watchAllTasks();
});

final activeTaskProvider = FutureProvider<PomodoroTask?>((ref) {
  return ref.watch(taskRepositoryProvider).getActiveTask();
});

final tasksByStatusProvider = FutureProvider.family<List<PomodoroTask>, TaskStatus>(
  (ref, status) => ref.watch(taskRepositoryProvider).getTasksByStatus(status),
);
```

### 3. Conversion between Drift rows and domain models

The repository converts between `TasksCompanion` (Drift) and `PomodoroTask` (Freezed). Enum fields stored as strings in SQLite, converted with `TaskPriority.values.byName(row.priority)`.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Can create a task with title, description, priority, and pomodoro estimate
- [ ] Can list all tasks, filter by status
- [ ] Setting a task active deactivates any previously active task
- [ ] Completing a task sets completedAt timestamp
- [ ] incrementPomodoros correctly updates count
- [ ] watchAllTasks stream emits on changes
- [ ] `flutter analyze` passes

