## Summary

Build the statistics service that aggregates session data for the efficiency report: daily focus distribution, total cycles, tomato counts, velocity metrics, and streaks.

## Implementation Details

### 1. Statistics Service (`lib/domain/services/statistics_service.dart`)

```dart
class StatisticsService {
  final SessionRepository sessionRepo;
  final TaskRepository taskRepo;

  /// Focus distribution by day of week (last 7 days)
  /// Returns map: dayOfWeek → {deepWork: minutes, logistics: minutes}
  Future<Map<int, DayFocusDistribution>> getWeeklyDistribution()

  /// Total completed focus cycles in a date range
  Future<int> getTotalCycles({DateTime? start, DateTime? end})

  /// "Tomatoes harvested" — completed focus sessions today
  Future<int> getTodayTomatoes()

  /// Weekly tomato count
  Future<int> getWeeklyTomatoes()

  /// Tomato goal progress (completed / daily goal)
  Future<(int completed, int goal)> getTomatoGoalProgress()

  /// Average session duration in minutes
  Future<double> getAverageSessionDuration()

  /// Peak productivity hour (hour with most completed sessions)
  Future<TimeOfDay?> getPeakTime()

  /// Break compliance: % of breaks that were actually taken
  Future<double> getBreakCompliance()

  /// Interruption rate: % of focus sessions abandoned before completion
  Future<String> getInterruptionRate()  // Returns "LOW", "MEDIUM", "HIGH"

  /// Consecutive days with at least 1 completed focus session
  Future<int> getDailyStreak()

  /// Week-over-week change in total cycles
  Future<double> getWeekOverWeekChange()  // e.g. 0.12 for +12%
}
```

### 2. Day focus distribution model

```dart
@freezed
class DayFocusDistribution {
  deepWorkMinutes: int     // Focus sessions linked to high-priority tasks
  logisticsMinutes: int    // Focus sessions linked to secondary/maintenance tasks or unlinked
}
```

Classification: sessions linked to `TaskPriority.high` tasks count as "deep work", everything else is "logistics".

### 3. Riverpod providers

```dart
final statisticsServiceProvider = Provider((ref) => StatisticsService(
  ref.watch(sessionRepositoryProvider),
  ref.watch(taskRepositoryProvider),
));

final weeklyDistributionProvider = FutureProvider((ref) =>
    ref.watch(statisticsServiceProvider).getWeeklyDistribution());

final totalCyclesProvider = FutureProvider((ref) =>
    ref.watch(statisticsServiceProvider).getTotalCycles());

final dailyStreakProvider = FutureProvider((ref) =>
    ref.watch(statisticsServiceProvider).getDailyStreak());

// ... etc for each metric
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Weekly distribution correctly categorizes deep work vs logistics
- [ ] Total cycles counts only completed focus sessions
- [ ] Peak time returns the most productive hour
- [ ] Break compliance calculation is accurate
- [ ] Daily streak tracks consecutive days correctly
- [ ] Week-over-week change computes correctly
- [ ] All providers resolve without errors
- [ ] `flutter analyze` passes

