## Summary

Implement the settings state management and persistence layer so user preferences (timer durations, auto-start, theme variant) are saved to the database and respected by the timer and theme.

## Implementation Details

### 1. Settings Repository (`lib/data/repositories/settings_repository.dart`)

```dart
class SettingsRepository {
  final AppDatabase db;

  /// Load settings (creates default row if none exists)
  Future<AppSettings> getSettings()

  /// Update a single field
  Future<void> updateFocusDuration(int minutes)
  Future<void> updateShortBreakDuration(int minutes)
  Future<void> updateLongBreakDuration(int minutes)
  Future<void> updateSessionsBeforeLongBreak(int count)
  Future<void> updateAutoStartBreaks(bool enabled)
  Future<void> updateHighContrastMode(bool enabled)
  Future<void> updateLayoutVariant(LayoutVariant variant)

  /// Reset all settings to defaults
  Future<void> resetToDefaults()

  /// Watch settings for reactive updates
  Stream<AppSettings> watchSettings()
}
```

### 2. Riverpod providers

```dart
final settingsRepositoryProvider = Provider((ref) =>
    SettingsRepository(ref.watch(databaseProvider)));

final settingsProvider = StreamProvider<AppSettings>((ref) {
  return ref.watch(settingsRepositoryProvider).watchSettings();
});

// Timer reads settings reactively
final focusDurationProvider = Provider<int>((ref) {
  return ref.watch(settingsProvider).valueOrNull?.focusDurationMinutes ?? 25;
});
```

### 3. Settings → Timer integration

The `TimerNotifier` watches settings. When focus duration changes while timer is idle, the displayed time updates. Changes during an active session take effect on the next session.

### 4. Settings → Theme integration

`highContrastMode` and `layoutVariant` are consumed by the theme provider (ticket #16). The settings screen toggles these and the theme updates reactively.

### 5. Reset functionality

"Reset System State" clears:
- All settings back to defaults
- Does NOT delete tasks or sessions (that's a separate destructive action)
- Shows a confirmation dialog before resetting

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Settings persist across app restarts
- [ ] Default settings are created on first launch
- [ ] Changing focus duration updates the timer display when idle
- [ ] watchSettings() stream emits on every change
- [ ] Reset to defaults works and shows confirmation
- [ ] `flutter analyze` passes
